history.content:
See the updated student answer @5621

Basically, the only way you'll get into the class, even if you fill out the CS Course Conflict Form, is if there's no one else on the waitlist who is eligible to enroll (either they're waitlisted for a full discussion, or they have a time conflict as well. In that case, you should get the SIS form to fill out.

Otherwise, what happens is that: you're the first on the waitlist, and space opens up. However, you have a conflict, so you'll have to be manually enrolled (through CS Course Conflict form). However, the waitlist will just skip over you and enroll the next eligible person, so there's not even an opportunity for someone to manually enroll you before the open space fills up.

Basically, unless the entire waitlist gets enrolled, you aren't likely to get into 170.

history.content:
I'd like to clarify the answer above. The waitlist processed 4 times a day (6:30am, 12:30pm, 6:30pm & 12:30am)  I usually process the CS Time Conflicts in between the 6:30am & 12:30pm WL processing. When I process that time conflict list, I am manually enrolling people into the class. If there are open seats during that time slot and you meet the reserve cap criteria then I will move you into the class.

Keep in mind that as the reserve caps come down, and (U)GSI hiring is done, I intermittently open more seats for a class. Both of these opportunities mean it's possible for me to process time conflicted students into the class before the WL automatically fills the seats again. So, while it is a smaller chance, it is not ALWAYS the case that you have to wait until everyone else on the WL gets in before you do.

I enrolled in CS 61C and waitlisted 170 in phase 1 -- I chose an open section for 170 that is now full, which is probably why I haven't got the SIS form pop up on Cal Central. I filled out the CS Course Conflict form, but it mentioned to fill that out after filling out the SIS form. Will being in a full section affect whether or not I get into the class -- ex. will the course conflict form manually put me into one of the open sections I chose? 

(I've looked through some of the questions on here about 170 and course conflicts, but am still not too sure what I need to do.) Thanks!
